  "description": [
    "So Labor May Know A new labor school dedicated to train ing trade union leaders for the nations of Africa and Asia has opened In Tel Aviv Israel with 70 students from 30 different countries For six months these students will be exposed to parallel programs in French and English covering a wide range of theoretical and practical courses on the role of trade unions in a democratic society and an insight as to how they can operate in the new conditions on these continents The AfroAsian Institute for Labor Studies sad Cooperation is a Joint ven ture of the Israel Federation of Labor Htotadrut and the AFLCIO The American Federations Executive Coun cil has voted to cover the costs of half the scholarship funds used to support students during their sixmonths train ing Htatadrut is operating the school and will cover the other half of the costa In a brochure describing the institute Hiatadrut declares he school has one simple purposeto train cadres for leadership in the labor movement of Asia and Africa Bat in addition to Its specific purpose of training personnel for the labor move ments of Africa and Asia the school is expected to provide a"
